Then re-test:

console.log($(".k-edit-form-container:visible").width());

If it jumps from 400 to around 850, we found the blocker.

If width is STILL 400

Inspect the editor container:

$(".k-edit-form-container:visible")[0]

Then run:

console.log(
    $(".k-edit-form-container:visible").attr("style")
);

I suspect Telerik is generating:

<div class="k-edit-form-container"
     style="width:400px">

If that's the case, CSS won't win because Telerik writes the width inline.

Then the fix is in the popup edit event:

function onStockCodedPartEdit(e) {

    e.container
        .find(".k-edit-form-container")
        .css({
            width: "100%",
            maxWidth: "none"
        });
}

